Only one of the two accused in the Brendin Horner murder has been granted bail. eNCA's Govan Whittles reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - One of the accused in the Brendin Horner murder case has been granted bail in the Senekal Magistrate Court. Sekola Matlaletsa has been granted R5,000 bail, while Sekwetje Mahlamba has been denied bail. READ: Ramaphosa: Senekal opened old wounds The two men are accused of murdering the 21-year-old farm manager. The matter has been postponed until 1 December for further investigation.